        "title": "Understanding the Balance of Flavors in Thai Cuisine",
        "content": "Thai cuisine is known for its unique balance of flavors: Sweet, Sour, Salty, and Spicy. Each flavor plays a crucial role in creating harmonious dishes. Explore how these flavors interact and complement each other.",
        "layout": "standard"
      },
      {
        "title": "Core Concepts of Thai Flavors",
        "content": "1. Sweet: Derived from palm sugar or fruits.  \n2. Sour: Commonly from lime juice or tamarind.  \n3. Salty: Enhances overall taste.  \n4. Spicy: Adds heat and depth.  \nUnderstanding these core concepts is essential for mastering Thai cooking.",
        "layout": "standard"
      },
      {
        "title": "Challenge Your Knowledge",
        "content": "Fill in the blanks using the clues from the flashcards and concepts covered in this module. Thai cuisine is known for its _______ balance of flavors, including _______ from palm sugar, _______ from lime juice, and _______ that enhances taste.",
        "layout": "standard"
      },
      {
        "title": "Quiz Yourself!",
        "content": "What flavor in Thai cuisine is often derived from palm sugar or fruits? Think about the core concepts of Thai cuisine you've learned.",
        "layout": "standard"
      }
    ]
  }
